&lt;p&gt;· Solders and desolders circuit board components effectively and efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Repairs complex specialty equipment at component level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Performs complex new product development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Communicates with customers and may travel to customer sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Designs fixtures and performs warranty root cause analysis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Reviews and edits complex repair processes and develops cycle time improvements.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Achieves year‑over‑year productivity increases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Takes responsibility in setting standards/methods for testing methodology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Processes required service report paperwork.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Assists less experienced technicians and provides direction and guidance and may provide backup for department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Evaluates components, including measurement of fits and tolerances, identification of parts required for replacement, and creates written work instructions for repair or testing needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Tests and certifies components including documentation of test results and writing test reports.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Documents work processes and instructions to ISO 9001 standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;· Participates in Quality Initiative; continually improves processes; quantitatively monitors processes. Completes required quality core classes and uses skills and techniques presented. Uses the Core Values in work environment. Adheres to company/customer safety procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
